This beauty was disassembled for a professional restoration five years ago,and was reassembled as a tribute to Mr. Shelby's 350. A painstaking refreshing of the entire car has recently been completed.The quality of the build is obvious wherever you look. The car has no rust and is built to stay that way.Body,engine compartment, undercarriage ,interior,and carpeted trunk are all pristine.The 289 V-8 was restored with a mild cam,a Holly dual feed carburator sits on an Edelbrock manifold.The correct tri-y headers empty into dual mufflers with just the right amount of rumble.Transmission is a rebuilt, smooth shifting three speed auto.Power steering and power disk brakes make driving a joy.The car rides on chrome five spoke Crager wheels,and new Firehawk tires. This is an investment grade show ready car that runs,looks,and drives as well as any you will find,with no issues or problems.

For sale is an original 1965 Mustang coupe. This is a rust free California car that was purchased in 2000 in California and driven back to Wisconsin.  The car has been garaged since then.
Black exterior and interior.
289ci V8 engine. C-4 automatic transmission.
Factory drum brakes with all new shoes, hardware, and wheel cylinders as well as a new dual bowl master cylinder.
New fuel tank and fuel lines installed last year.
Autolite 2100 2v carburetor recently rebuilt.  Hot air choke replaced with electric choke.
New starter, plug wires, coil, starter solenoid, voltage regulator, and Petronix electronic ignition.
Car had factory air conditioning that is not currently operational but original compressor is included.
Interior has all new vinyl seat covers, a new dash pad, and new carpet.  There is a slight discoloring of the carpet near the shifter.  The headliner is white and has several blemishes.
An appraisal was done in April of 2016 with an estimated value of $15,000.  Asking $14,000 with reasonable offers accepted.

Beautiful 1964 and a half Mustang convertible for sale. The car is a very rare Guardsman blue color. This color was only available for the first 6 months of production and was the color Carlo Shelby used for the blue stripes on the original Shelby GT 350. The car has a blue interior with a white convertible top.

The engine is the 289 D-code V8. The car has a 4 speed manual transmission and dual exhausts. The interior seats and carpet are like new and look great. It has seatbelts installed in the front and back for safety. Mounted on the steering column is an original, working, rally pack. The shifter knob is a light up “Flameball” that looks great at night and the original shifter knob comes with the car.
The car was upgraded with a steering and suspension upgrade kid, the “Grad a Track – Super Started Kit” kit from Mustangs Plus. The Kit included:
A Stock Plus Spring and Handling Kit:
4-Leaf Standard Eye Leaf Springs (upgraded to 4 1/2 reverse eye leafs)
Coil Springs (upgrade to 1'” drop)
1" Front Sway Bar Kit (upgraded to 1 1,4 sway bar)
4 Standard U-Bolts
Pair Of Spring Eye Bolts
Polyurethane Coil Spring Insulator Pads
Front & Rear Shock Absorbers (upgraded to Edelbrock shocks)
Steel Shackles w/Rubber Bushings (upgraded to all urethane bushings)
A Performance Suspension Rebuild Kit:
Upper Control Arms
Lower Control Arms
Spring Perches
Polyurethane Strut Rod Bushings
A Make-it-New Steering Rebuild Kit:
Inner & Outer Tie Rod Ends
Adjusting sleeves
Idler arm

The car was dropped about 2 inches all around to give it a great stance. The car also has 15 inch American Racing wheels and performance tires. The car comes with the original styled steel wheels so it can be returned to stock any time. A new 600 cfm Edelbrock carburetor was added along with an oval air cleaner. Again, the car comes with the original autolite carb. Also added were kick panel speakers and a 100 disc CD changer located in the truck with the radio and tuner in the glove box. The radio can be controlled by a remote control without the need to open the  glove box.

This car runs and drives great. The engine pulls strong and the car sticks to the road nicely with all of the suspension and steering upgrades. This is not a 100 point show car but is a really nice driver. The paint and interior look great and the car gets complements everywhere it goes.
If you are looking for a car that you can just get in and go this is it! The rare Guardsman blue color along with the wheels and lowered stance really makes this mustang stand out from the rest.

For sale in our Houston showroom is a classic American automobile known as the Ford Mustang. This 1965 convertible is fully restored and ready for new adventures if you are bold enough to sit in the drivers seat. Under the Ice Blue hood sits the original 289 CID V8 engine backed by a 3-spd automatic transmission. As a multiple show winner heres your chance to skip the long costly experience of a restoration and buy one that is turn-key ready. This way you can avoid the 100+ conversations of yes dear I will have all of the mustang parts out of the kitchen sink and the car completed next summer. The gloss Ice Blue paint offer black GT striping and inside is Pony interior that is blue and black vinyl. Fully loaded the Mustang offer AC (upgraded 134a) power steering power brakes(disc) and power windows. This is no base model. This Pony has only seen trips to car shows and warm sunny day cruises and afterwards back in the garage she quietly slept awaiting the next adventure. Brand new red line BFG tires break up the blue and present period correct styling. The Mustang will always be one of the first cars that pops up in the imagination of a car enthusiast when they hear the words ??American Muscle.? Heres your chance at owning a fully restored piece of history. It is almost like being given the chance to buy something from a history museum and use it! To view the car in greater detail including an HD video of the Mustang running and driving please visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com or our Houston showroom.
